rk. See the measurements and bundle cost of each import."],[105,"Expected ID type (auto-detected if omitted)"],[376,"Export"],[121,"For a Deno project without a package import map, use Deno's npm specifier directly:"],[21,"For an exact pin, set `UNIKU_VERSION` to a version from the GitHub releases page, without the `uniku-cli-v` tag prefix."],[311,"From `@owpz/ksuid`"],[310,"From `@paralleldrive/cuid2`"],[312,"From `bson`"],[307,"From `nanoid`"],[313,"From `tsid-ts`"],[309,"From `typeid-js`"],[308,"From `ulid`"],[306,"From `uuid`"],[314,"From `xid-ts` or `nexid`"],[4,"Generate"],[66,"Generate CUIDs (v2)."],[73,"Generate KSUIDs."],[78,"Generate MongoDB ObjectIDs."],[44,"Generate monotonically increasing ULIDs"],[56,"Generate Nanoids."],[84,"Generate TSIDs: 64-bit Snowflake-style, time-sorted identifiers."],[49,"Generate TypeIDs: a UUID v7 with a type prefix."],[40,"Generate ULIDs."],[31,"Generate UUIDs (v4 or v7)."],[79,"Generate XIDs compatible with rs/xid."],[2,"Generate, inspect, and validate IDs from the terminal."],[228,"Generation speed"],[231,"Generation speed is a primary design constraint in uniku. In the current CI snapshot, every one of its ten strategies beats the dedicated npm implementation it targets. The smallest measured lead is 1.2× for UUID v4 and ObjectID; ULID reaches 116×."],[235,"Generator"],[384,"Generator arguments are invalid: bad size, alphabet, length, timestamp, or version."],[373,"Generator list"],[348,"Generator references"],[113,"Getting started"],[199,"Go rs/xid compatibility"],[213,"Hono request IDs with Nanoid"],[217,"Hono's request ID middleware accepts a synchronous `generator`. When a request does not already carry a valid `X-Request-Id` header, this example generates a compact Nanoid, stores it in the request context, and returns it in the response header."],[98,"ID type: `uuid`, `ulid`, `typeid`, `nanoid`, `cuid`, `ksuid`, `objectid`, `xid`, `tsid` (auto-detected if omitted)"],[208,"If you create records in more than one service or need an ID before inserting a row, start with UUID v7. It is a UUID-native value, sort-friendly, and uses a familiar database column type."],[327,"Implied by which `isValid` matches: `uuidv4.isValid` accepts only version 4, `uuidv7.isValid` accepts only version 7."],[261,"Import"],[351,"Import"],[425,"Independent runtimes choose their identity randomly, so uniqueness across them remains probabilistic rather than host-anchored as in Go's `rs/xid` implementation."],[14,"Inspect"],[3,"Install"],[115,"Install"],[303,"Install @uniku/cli when you need an ID in a terminal, migration, or shell pipeline. It shares the library's formats but has its own release lifecycle."],[114,"Install ten type-safe ID strategies, then import only the generator your application needs."],[17,"Installs the current standalone binary without requiring Node.js:"],[211,"Integrations"],[305,"Keep familiar formats while moving to direct, portable imports."],[10,"ksuid"],[153,"KSUID"],[249,"KSUID"],[395,"KSUID"],[397,"KSUID combines a timestamp with a large random payload. Choose it for high-volume distributed systems that need chronological order and a 27-character URL-safe string."],[62,"Length of the ID, 1-256 (default: `21`)"],[72,"Length of the ID, 2-32 (default: `24`)"],[198,"Matches MongoDB's 12-byte ObjectID format."],[201,"Matches rs/xid's compact 12-byte text and binary format."],[304,"Migrate from other libraries"],[334,"Migrate to uniku v1"],[315,"Migration is usually an import change first. Keep the stored identifier format stable, then move generation behind the new direct entry point. Every example below shows the value returned by the uniku generator."],[262,"Minified + gzipped"],[196,"MongoDB `_id` compatibility"],[403,"MongoDB-compatible 12-byte identifiers."],[392,"Most generator modules re-export all four classes, so you rarely need to import from `uniku/errors` directly. Nanoid and CUID v2, which have no binary codec, only re-export `InvalidInputError` and `UniqueIdError`."]